Malachite walks ahead of Polaris as they reach the theatre, holding the door open for him.
"M'lord."

He lets out a sigh, “Stop that. I’m not *close* to a lord.”
He was a bit trembly. Now that he was aware of this whole *mind reading* thing, the thoughts of others grew that much louder. It was a bit overbearing.
"You alright?"

“Yeah. Just.. Been a while since I went out. What’s showing?”
He entered the theater, looking around curiously.
((**jesus actual christ**
(sggxunenxjdnjdn)
"I don't watch animated movies at the theatre too often, so I'm not really sure  off the top of my head. You can go check while I'm buying us drinks."

“S-Sure... okay,” he mumbled, nodding. He wasn’t looking forward to standing around looking at pictures on the wall like an idiot for 10 minutes, but what can ya do? He headed towards the movie options.

"Want any soda? Diet cola?"
He calls from across the room.
He turns around, startled by how Malachite is just carelessly shouting at a public place, and he summons Star, sending the other over to him and shoving a finger over his mouth.
“*You’re being loud. Diet cola, please.*”

"This place is pretty empty, but alright."
He gives him a thumbs up and starts filling up the cups.
"*There's still people in here..*" Star mutters, as if Polaris had forgotten the others can't see stands.

"It's fine, Lari."
Hierophant ruffles Star Platinum's hair affectionately.
"Should we get popcorn?"

"They have popcorn here..?" Polaris murmurs to himself, ignoring the anxiety that comes with saying that out loud.
"*Sure.*"

"Cool."
He gives him another thumbs up and approaches the counter.

Star follows closely behind, almost like a lost puppy.
"*There's... Trolls, It, Onward, Birds of Prey.. What's 'It' about?*"

"It's scary. You'd hate it."
He crouches down to check out the candy, pushing his sunglasses to they front of his nose to peer at the selection.
"What kind of popcorn do you want?"

"*Scary.. how? Buttered, please.*"
Star looked curious.

"It has a clown monster."
He grins as he notices they have sour cherry candy. *Fuck yeah.*
"...Hey, Polaris?"
"*I've never seen a real clown before...*" Star mumbled, before hearing Malachite again. "*Yeah?*"
"Why don't you just read my thoughts? Then I don't have to talk to myself."

"*Oh, sorry, uh. Lemme see if Star can... do that,*" he stuttered out, actually having forgotten other muns can't see Stands.
"*Try thinking stuff, let's see if Star can hear it.*"

"Mhm."
*Hello?*
"*..Hm. I can hear you through Star, but it's a little muffled. Should do, though. 'It' sounds interesting. How do you turn clowns scary?*"

***Big teeth.***
He stands up, pointing to the candy he wants and taking out his wallet.
***Fucked up shark clown.***
"*I have big teeth. I like sharks.*"

***Not like you.***
He counts out the money he owes and sets it on the counter along with their drinks.
***Your's are cuter.***
"*Mine are big. And very sharp. Why are you so against it?*"
***You Will Not Like It.***

"*For the past one million seven hundred thousand years I have only watched animated movies for children and drama TV shows for teenagers who want to watch 'adult shows'. I want to try something different.*"
***Do you want to watch It? Do you want that?***
"*Sure. Looks intense.*"

***Okay.***
He approaches the counter again.
"Two tickets for *"It"*, please?"
"*What's It about?*"
***A demon clown that kills people.***
//um ackshually it's an alien
((akdkaksjdsjdj
"*Huh. A clown that kills people. Does anyone kill the clown?*"
***I think so***

"*Cool. Happy endings are nice.*"
Star decides to float behind Malachite, wrapping it's arms in front of him to hold on and burrying its chin in the crook of his neck.
He hums, using Hierophant to stroke Star's hair.
Polaris purrs from where's he's standing, but immediately stops himself to keep from embarrassing himself in public. He clears his throat quickly, shuffling over to Malachite.

"Mmm, so you're sure about It?"
He gets closer to him, putting an arm around his waist.
"I still think you'll hate it."
"I'll try something new," he shrugs. "I don't really know the story, and this is the second movie, but whatever."

"Alright."
This *could* be an excuse for Malachite to wrap his arm around Polaris' shoulders in a comforting gesture, therefore checking off a box on the list of Important Couple Cliches. Excellent.
“You think I’m going to get scared,” he states bluntly, raising a brow at that thought.
"I think you *might.* Do you want to go to the actual room now?"
“Mhm,” he nods, having star take hold of the popcorn and a cup so that Malachite doesn’t drop anything.
He leads him to the showing of It, holding the door open again.

He moves his hand high above Malachite’s pushing the door open further.
“Ladies first.”

He bats his eyelashes. 
"Very chivalrous of you, Polaris, but I insist."

“...”
He summons Star, the stand taking Malachite’s wrist and moving it off of the door, floating forward into the room and tugging Malachite with it.
“So do I.”

"Hey- let me be a gentleman!"
Hierophant clings to the door.
Polaris enters the room after Star pulls Malachite in, letting the door shut behind him with a soft *thump*. “You already were. My turn.”

He huffs, dusting himself off.
"You're lucky I love you so much."
He hums, sauntering back toward Polaris and grabbing his arm.

“Ah—“
Star Platinum disappears with a small “ora!” and a light wave, fading into nothingness.

"Shall we?"
He tugs him lightly down the aisle, toward the seats.
"Oooh, it's mostly empty. Lucky us."
“Mhm. Still a few people, though. We should be quiet,” he whispers, letting Malachite pull him wherever. So they just.. Sit down and watch the movie? Okay then.

"It's best to sit in the middle,"
He explains quietly, releasing Polaris' arm and shuffling down one of the rows before taking his seat.
“Makes sense,” he nods, following Malachite and taking the seat next to him, placing the popcorn in Malachite’s lap and putting his soda in the cupholder next to him.

"Ooh, good timing,"
He murmurs, looking up at the screen.
"Look- they're dimming the lights. That means we missed the ads; the movie's starting."
“They have ads?” he asks, still whispering and turning his head to Malachite.

"Mhm."
He sips at his cherry cola, then gestures to the screen with the cup.
"Ah- the movie's starting."

“Oh,” he breathes out, turning his head to the movie. He was.. a bit excited, actually. There’s a little bit of euphoria that comes with new experiences, and this was something that he should’ve experienced by this point.. He was happy.

He takes Polaris' hand, still a bit concerned that the movie will upset him.
"Let me know if anything bothers you, alright?"
“I will. Don’t worry, Malachite,” he reassures, gripping Malachite’s hand back. Don’t want to concern Malachite, after all.
(I've never seen this movie lmao what the fuck is it about)
((uhhh lemme dm you
He glances over at Polaris, then turns his attention back to the movie, giving his hand a reassuring squeeze.

"You doing alright?"
He turns to Polaris part of the way through the beginning. He knows he's not overly fond of violence, and isn't sure how much it extends to movies.
“Mhm. It’s.. bloody, but it’s fine,” he says, gripping Malachite’s hand again. He was forcing himself not to tremble. He is *not* sensitive.
"You sure?"

“Yes.”
He’s firm with the word, though he tries not to be. He winces a bit when pennywise does.. *that* to the little girl. It’s. Uh. *Vulgar.*

"Mhm..."
*Bull shit. He doesn't believe a word of that.*
“I’m fine. Really,” he whispers, turning his gaze to Malachite.
He looks at him, concerned, but finally sighs and continues watching the movie.
By the time the next jumpscare pops up, he’s already dissociated. He grips Malachite’s hand hard, but doesn’t do much other than that.

He squeezes back, brow furrowed with worry.
"Polaris?"
He zones back in, his previously dot-like pupils getting larger after doing so. “Y-Yeah, I’m fine. Sorry. Spaced out a bit..”

"If you don't like it, we can leave."
His tone is dead serious.
“No. *No.* I’m fine. Just spaced out.”

He relents again, but he's still a bit doubtful. He *really* doesn't want Polaris' first time going to the theatre to be overly upsetting. He sighs and settles for holding onto Polaris' arm, resting his head on his shoulder.

“...”
Polaris turns his gaze to Malachite, appreciating the warmth that the other offered in the otherwise too-cold theater room, and he smiled, giving Malachite his silent thanks. He returns his attention to the movie, though he forcefully dissociates again quickly after.

Blood spatters across the screen again, and Malachite decides enough is enough. Polaris clearly isn't enjoying this, which defeats the *entire purpose* of them going to the theatre in the first place.
"Polaris, let's go, alright?"
He gently nudges him, looking away from the screen.

“? Why? What’s wrong?”
He turned his had to Malachite, having snapped back into reality from the nudge.
"You clearly aren't enjoying it."

“...”
He wanted to say he was, but.. Honestly, it was a struggle to pay attention to the movie. He pouted.
“..Alright..”

He stands up and ruffles Polaris' hair, then extends a hand to help him up.
"We can find another movie to watch."
"It's fine," he whispers, still not wanting to disrupt the other people there, as he takes Malachite's hand and stands up.
"Mhm. You like cartoons, so we can find something animated, if you want."

"..."
*I feel bad..*
"You had to buy those tickets and sit here with me. I'm sorry."
"Wh- hey, no, you're fine. I'm sorry for not buying tickets to a better movie."
"I'm the one who asked for it. We can just head back home, sorry to make you pay," he suggests as he begins walking out.
"You didn't make me do anything, Polaris. I suggested it."
"I'm the one who picked it."
*"I* wasn't the one who hated it. It's fine, I promise."
“Mm.. Let’s just go back home.”
"Do you *want* to go back home?"
He shrugged. “Sure.”
"But do you *want* to?"
“No point in staying.”
"We can see another movie, if you want."
He turned back to Malacnite. “It’s fine, really.”
"It's- what do you want to do? What would make you *happy?"*

“...”
He stopped, looking down at the ground like it’d give him all the answers he needed. After a few breaths, he turned back to Malachite.
“I don’t know what I want.”

"..."
He looks at him, sadness flickering behind his eyes for a moment.
"...That's alright."
He absently fiddles with a piece of his hair, thinking.
"There's nothing that would make you happy right now? Nothing specific?"
“I don’t know. Nothing I can think of,” he shrugs. “Never got to figure out what I’d want to do.”

He swallows back a little glimmer of rage. There's time for that later.
"...We can figure it out then. That sound good?"
He puts on a smile, tilting his head.
"We can find you some hobbies."
“Mhm, okay,” he nods, trying to match Malachite’s enthusiasm.
"Let's see what they have playing, alright?"

“Ok..”
He reached his hand forward a bit, wanting to take Mala’s but deciding against it, bringing it back to his side quickly. He didn’t need someone to hold his hand for him.

He notices the small gesture and grabs his hand.
"You alright?"

“Mhm.”
He grips Malachite’s hand back. “I.. feel like I’ve been left out most of my life. It’s weird.”
"Well, you... *have* been."
“I have?”
"Well, yeah. You were... pretty isolated."
“...It still feels weird realizing this..” he mumbles, looking down. He’s never gonna get used to this fact.

"Makes sense."
He moves closer, lightly bumping his head against his arm.
"Must be hard... I'm sorry you have to go through this shit."

He shrugs. “It’s fine. I think I’m used to it.”
*I wonder what I would be doing right now if I had never met Malachite..*

"That doesn't mean it's good."
He frowns a bit, sticking his tongue out slightly in a thoughtful manner.
“When you get used to something, it stops feeling like anything, really,” he shrugged again. “Whether it’s good or bad, it’s my normal.”
"Well, wouldn't you rather things feel good?"

“...”
He stayed silent for a moment.
“I.. don’t have much to go off of what feels ‘good’. When I kiss you, I feel ‘good’, but I think that’s.. not the same good as what you mean.”

*Jesus.* Malachite is channelling all his energy toward Not Thinking About what he's going to do to the Plasma when he meets them next.
"You were cheated out of a childhood, and I'll be damned if I don't help you get it back."
He forces his voice to sound cheerful, but it quavers a bit.
He looked at Malachite, stars in his widened eyes and.. a little excited. “Then, uh, show the way, I guess.”

"Alright, you said you like cartoons, right? Let's start there."
He's put the smooth lightness back over his voice. He is not angry. He is not upset. He is not going to think about how he wants to rip Morise's arm off and feed it to them.
"What movies are showing?"

“I think I remember.. There’s Trolls, Onward, Birds of Prey...”
He tried thinking harder, furrowing his brow as he did. “That’s.. all I remember..”

"...Based on what I've heard, I think Onward is our best bet."
He hooks his arm through Polaris' and smiles up at him.
"Sound good?"
He turns to Malachite, squeezing his arm a bit and nodding. “Mhm. Looked colorful.”

"Alright."
He leads him over to the front desk and requests two tickets, as well as another bag of popcorn.

“Oh— I forgot the popcorn in the other room,” he remembers when Malachite orders a bag of popcorn. 
“Let me pay you back for this.” He reaches into his back pocket, searching around for his wallet.
"Hey- you don't need to. I've got it."
Once his wallet is found, he takes it out. “Mala, come on. You already payed once..”
"I'm a savior too, remember? I don't make as much as you, but I can certainly pay for popcorn."
“You already paid though,” he repeats.
"But I can pay again."
“Why would you need to?”

He takes some money out of his wallet and sets it on the counter, looking up at Polaris with faux innocence.
"Oops, looks like I already payed. Oh well."

“...”
He just gaped at Malachite with betrayal as the poor theatre employee slowly took the moment.
“I’m paying you back when we get home.”
"No."
“Yes.”

"Just let me do this, Polaris,"
He sticks his tongue out a little.

“...”
He bends down and kisses Malachite without warning, not exactly knowing how else to get back at him in that very moment.
He hums in surprise and squeezes his hand a little.

After a moment, he leans back.
“I’m getting you back, later,” is all he says.

He glows brighter, cocking his head at him.
"Oh, *scary.* I'm terrified, Lari."

After a moment, he realizes why that might not be such a good idea.
“Oh. Then no cuddles, I guess,” he shrugs, walking towards the side of the counter you pick up your popcorn and soda from.

"Wh- hey, wait!"
He walks after him quickly, heeled boots tapping on the tile.
*Clickclickclick* "That's not fair!"
“How else can I get you back? Obviously kissing you doesn’t work.”

"I'm trying to be nice,"
He complains, looking up toward him.
"Why won't you let me do this?"
“Well, I work hard so that I can pay for you guys. What am I supposed to do with the money otherwise?”

"I work hard too,"
He protests.
“You don’t *have* to, though..” he says, turning around and meeting Malachite’s gaze.

"Maybe I want to."
He holds eye contact stubbornly.
"Let me pay for things."

“...”
He has an idea.
Quickly, he stops time, having Star reach over and grab Malachite’s wallet from his pocket, putting it in his own back pocket, and resuming time again.
“Fine. Sure.”

"Thank you."
He smiles, eyes twinkling triumphantly.
"I'm going to go get some more candies, do you want any?"
“What is there?”

He shrugs.
"M&Ms, Junior mints... some other shit. You can come look, if you want."
“Hm. M&Ms sound good. Are they chocolate?”
"Mhm. They have crunchy candy around them."
He hummed. “Sure. I’ll have some.”

"Alright."
He shoots him a finger gun and saunters away to buy some candies.

He nods, turning away and letting himself crack a smile.
*Wait. Am I pranking Malachite? Have I ever pranked somebody before..?* he asked himself, blinking a few times in surprise.

He orders the snacks and reaches into his wallet to pay for th- wait. *Wait.*
"...Son of a *fuck."*

“..*Pfft.*”
He covers his face with his hand, making sure to not let out any loud sound. Right after, he clears his throat, pulling out his tesseract and fiddling with it idly.

"Polaris?"
He furrows his brow after patting himself down a few times, then looks over at him incredulously.
*"Polaris?"*
“Hm?” he hums, turning to Malachite and pulling his best pokerface.

"...Have you seen my wallet?"
*He **didn't.***

He shook his head no. “Did you lose it?”
*Gotta ease into offering to pay.*

"I guess? I don't know when it would've happened though, I just had it..."
Polaris couldn't have... no, definitely not.
He paused for a second. “Maybe you left it in the movie room..? You can go look while I pay for the food,” he offers, pulling out his own wallet.

"I just used it to buy popcorn though! Maybe I dropped it...?"
He crouches down onto his hands and knees, peeking around on the floor.
He shrugs. “Let’s look for it after I pay for the candy,” he says, going up to the counter and passing the employee (who eyes Polaris for a solid second) a few bills.

"Wait- I want to find my wallet."
He continues searching around on the floor.
"I can pay."
“No, it’s fine, I got the candy already,” he says, turning around and passing Malachite a pack of M&Ms.

"I... hm."
He sits cross-legged on the floor, taking the M&Ms and tossing one into his mouth.

After a moment, he stops time again and takes the wallet out, lightly passing it onto the floor somewhere a bit behind Malachite, going back into his previous position and resuming time once more.

He opens up his own M&Ms and munches on some. “Hm. Chocolatey.”

"Glad you like them..."
He munches on another handful, then puts the bad into his pocket and continues searching.
"Ah- it's here?"
He picks it up, looking a bit confused.
"I think I would've seen that..."
He shrugs. “You probably just missed it. The floor is kinda brightly colored here.”

"...I guess I am wearing sunglasses..."
It still rubs him the wrong way, but he brushes it aside.
"Let me pay you for the candy."

“Nah, I already payed for it. No point giving me money now.”
He puts his wallet in his back pocket, patting it to make sure it’s actually in there.

"It's the principle."
He pulls some munny out of the wallet, offering it to Polaris.
“No,” is all he says, refusing to take the money. He keeps his hands in his pockets.

His expression hardens, and Hierophant unfurls out of nowhere, taking the money and trying to slide it into Polaris' pocket.
"Take it."
He backs up, Star Platinum appearing and grabbing the appendage, holding it still. “だが断る.”

"Fine, I'll just buy more candy."
He stands, turning to the poor cashier.
"Lemonheads, please."

Star Platinum grabs Malachite, lifting the other up over it’s shoulder and carrying him towards Polaris, much to the fear and confusion of the employee. “Let’s go watch the movie,” is all he says, turning around and heading towards the screening room.

"Wh- hEY!"
he struggles for a moment before sighing in resignation and going limp.
“*There, there,*” Star coos, patting Malachite on the behind. “*I’m paying for everything else tonight, okay?*”

"I- wh- you can't *do* that."
He protests weakly.
“*I’m sorry, who is currently ass up in the air right now?*”

He's cut off, breath hitching.
"I-"
“*That’s what I thought,*” Star cuts him off, patting his butt again. Thank *god* the theatre is mostly empty, or else Polaris would *never* do this. Still, it’s entertaining.

"..."
Malachite is stunned into silence. *How... how is he supposed to react to this?*

“...I kinda see why you like teasing me so much. It’s fun,” Polaris chuckles a bit, slowing down a bit so he’s walking behind Star Platinum, facing Malachite. He offers Malachite a small, smug yet guilty smile.

*So this is what it feels like...? He'll keep that in mind in the future.*
"Alright, you can have your fun for today. I'm paying you back for this though."
“I thought I was gonna pay you back..?” he asked, tilting his head and giving a confused, innocent face.
"I- you- you *did.* You bought the candy."
“That’s not what I meant.”

He paused, Star pausing in front of him.
“It’s.. weird, seeing you like this. Quiet, I mean.”

"...Mhm."
What the *fuck?* He's glad Polaris has the confidence to do this, *especially* in public, but... ***What the fuck?*** How does he react to this? He tries to find words, but just ends up stammering out a few syllables and lighting up like a lava lamp.

*Oh shit—*
“A-ah, Mala, you okay? I didn’t go too far right?”
He began to get nervous. Sure this was *fun* but Malachite’s comfort was his top priority and he was *not* completely sure Malachite was comfortable in this situation.

"N-no, it's fine."
His brain feels like it's short circuiting, but it's not a *bad* thing. Especially if this is what Polaris wants.

“...”
Star Platinum readjusts Malachite, placing him down on his feet and holding him still, making sure he won’t just fall over before it sticks out its tongue at him and disappears. Polaris rushes up to Malachite, holding his hands out, wanting to hold Malachite but also not wanting to freak him out. “You sure..? You’re lighting up..?

He nods, swallowing. 
"Mmhm, it's good. Don't worry about it."
“...I don’t believe you. You’re never so flustered, no matter how hard I try to tease you. I didn’t get you sick.. right?” he asks, placing the back of his hand on Malachite’s forehead.

He rubs his forehead against the back of his hand, a low purr building in his chest.
"Mm, I'm not sick."

“You sure..? We can head back home if you don’t feel good..”
Polaris’ brow furrowed, worried. *I... I didn’t go too far, right?*

"N-no, it's fine."
Malachite feels like his bones are melting.

“I usually trust you but...”
He scoops up Malachite, holding his legs under one hand and his upper back on the other. “You don’t seem well. I’m taking you home.”

He yelps.
"Wait- I'm not sick! I promise, this is normal."
He pouts at Malachite, worried, as he begins walking towards the exit. “I don’t trust that.”

"We- we were going to watch a movie."
He looks a little deflated, slightly upset his idea didn't go as planned.
"You said you like cartoons..."

“It’s fine.”
*I care more about you being okay than I ever will about some cartoon.*
“I just want you to be okay. Let’s go home.”

"I promise I'm not sick."
He mumbles, his energy kinda smooshed out of him. Being carried around and passed back and forth like a doll seems to have that effect, apparently.

He sighs. They can see a movie another day.
"...Sure. Alright."
